t worth noting as a gap.\\\\n\\\",\\\"created\\\":\\\"2026-03-13T12:22:14Z\\\",\\\"id\\\":2930880439,\\\"line\\\":170,\\\"path\\\":\\\"cmd/entire/cli/login.go\\\",\\\"state\\\":\\\"line\\\"}\\n{\\\"author\\\":\\\"Copilot\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"`DisallowUnknownFields()` on the poll response will cause a hard error if the server adds any new fields to the OAuth token response. For the `/oauth/token` endpoint especially, servers commonly return additional fields (e.g., `refresh_token`, `id_token`). Consider removing `DisallowUnknownFields()` from `decodeJSON` (or at least from the poll path) to be forward-compatible with server-side changes.\\\",\\\"created\\\":\\\"2026-03-13T12:22:15Z\\\",\\\"id\\\":2930880476,\\\"line\\\":null,\\\"path\\\":\\\"cmd/entire/cli/auth/client.go\\\",\\\"state\\\":\\\"line\\\"}\\n{\\\"author\\\":\\\"Copilot\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Same issue: `DisallowUnknownFields()` on the auth store `Load()` will reject the file if any new field is added in a future CLI version. This makes it impossible to evolve the auth file format without breaking older CLI versions. Consider removing this restriction for forward compatibility.\\\\n\\\",\\\"created\\\":\\\"2026-03-13T12:22:15Z\\\",\\\"id\\\":2930880495,\\\"line\\\":null,\\\"path\\\":\\\"cmd/entire/cli/auth/store.go\\\",\\\"state\\\":\\\"line\\\"}\\n{\\\"author\\\":\\\"cursor[bot]\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"### `DisallowUnknownFields` breaks on OAuth server extra fields\\\\n\\\\n**High Severity**\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003c!-- DESCRIPTION START --\\\\u003e\\\\n`decodeJSON` uses `DisallowUnknownFields()` when decoding external OAuth API responses. OAuth token responses (RFC 6749 §5.1) commonly include fields like `refresh_token` that aren't in the `DeviceAuthPoll` struct, and both RFC 8628 and RFC 6749 explicitly allow servers to add extension parameters. Any extra field from the server will cause a hard decode error, breaking the login flow. The integration tests don't catch this because the mock server returns only the exact fields in the struct.\\\\n\\\\u003c!-- DESCRIPTION END --\\\\u003e\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003c!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: 6a8b0884-0c23-43c7-aab8-fbef4722b77b --\\\\u003e\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003c!-- LOCATIONS START\\\\ncmd/entire/cli/auth/client.go#L164-L178\\\\nLOCATIONS END --\\\\u003e\\\\n\\\\u003cdiv\\\\u003e\\\\u003ca href=\\\\\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" rel=\\\\\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\\\\\"\\\\u003e\\\\u003cpicture\\\\u003e\\\\u003csource media=\\\\\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\\\\\" srcset=\\\\\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\\\\\"\\\\u003e\\\\u003csource media=\\\\\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\\\\\" srcset=\\\\\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\\\\\"\\\\u003e\\\\u003cimg alt=\\\\\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\\\\\" width=\\\\\\\"115\\\\\\\" height=\\\\\\\"28\\\\\\\" src=\\\\\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\\\\\"\\\\u003e\\\\u003c/picture\\\\u003e\\\\u003c/a\\\\u003e\\\\u0026nbsp;\\\\u003ca href=\\\\\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" rel=\\\\\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\\\\\"\\\\u003e\\\\u003cpicture\\\\u003e\\\\u003csource media=\\\\\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\\\\\" srcset=\\\\\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\\\\\"\\\\u003e\\\\u003csource media=\\\\\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\\\\\" srcset=\\\\\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\\\\\"\\\\u003e\\\\u003cimg alt=\\\\\\\"Fix in Web\\\\\\\" width=\\\\\\\"99\\\\\\\" height=\\\\\\\"28\\\\\\\" src=\\\\\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\\\\\"\\\\u003e\\\\u003c/picture\\\\u003e\\\\u003c/a\\\\u003e\\\\u003c/div\\\\u003e\\\\n\\\\n\\\",\\\"created\\\":\\\"2026-03-13T12:26:19Z\\\",\\\"id\\\":2930899206,\\\"line\\\":188,\\\"path\\\":\\\"cmd/entire/cli/auth/client.go\\\",\\\"state\\\":\\\"line\\\"}\\n{\\\"author\\\":\\\"cursor[bot]\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"### RFC 8628 `slow_down` requires 5-secon